markets.title: Will federal employees be prohibited from editing Wikipedia this year?
markets.rules_primary: If the President of the United States issues any executive order, signs any bill into law, or if the Presidential administration otherwise takes any formal action which is aimed at banning employees of the U.S. federal government from editing or drafting Wikipedia articles during working hours or using federal property before Dec 31, 2025, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.early_close_condition: This market will close and expire early if the event occurs.
